Kari, I think that tolerance means refraining from agressions against other people. It doesn´t mean approval or complicity. Since nobody appointed me as judge of other people, I can´t act as executioner, either. If some restrictions must be applied to the liberty of other people, let it be done by legal and fair process, with due care. There´s always the possibility of being wrong, and punishing the inocent. There´s also a big probability of unfairness, of punishing a few and letting a lot of others, many of which are maybe as guilty as the punished ones or even more guilty, go unmolested. I insist in that often there´s a very serious social problem underlying antisocial conduct, and punishment is at best a partial solution, at worst no solution at all.

Rodrigo

