The establishment clause for those who are not familiar with the US Constitution comes from the 1st Amendment:

&quot;Congress shall make no law respecting an establishment of religion ...&quot;

The problem comes in where people think that celebrating Christmas in schools, or in City Hall is the government attempting to &quot;establish&quot; a state religion. BS, as far as I'm concerned. When my ability to practice my religion anywhere (as long as I am not trying to force my beliefs on someone else) is being restricted because of a misinterpretation of the 1st amendment, that is, in actuality, the government establishing a &quot;Religion of Atheism&quot;, and IMHO is in itself a violation of the 1st Amendment.

The 1st Amendment is a &quot;Hand's off Religion&quot; amendment. The government should have, IMHO, no connection whatsoever with religion one way or another.....except to intervene when one group tries to impose its beliefs upon another.

Namaste
